Sustainable tourism development, its patterns, principles and their practical application in tourism management. Strengths and challenges of tourism as a tool for sustainable development. Key actors in the sustainable tourism. Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of this course is to introduce the patterns and concepts of sustainable tourism development, the principles of sustainable tourism management, and their application in different types of tourism, as well as to discuss the barriers and challenges of sustainable development that arise in the tourism industry.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) understands the different dimensions of sustainable tourism, including social, economic, and environmental aspects; 2) determines the goals, strengths, and obstacles of sustainable tourism development; 3) identifies the key actors in sustainable tourism to understand the role and possibilities of each stakeholder in contributing to the development of sustainable tourism.
